\begin{definition}[Stagnation point]
    We call the zeros of a vector field $u\colon X\to\R^d$ \emph{stagnation points}.
    The stagnation points of $u=\nabla f$ are called \emph{critical points} of $f\colon X\to\R$.
  \end{definition}
